{"schema_version":"1","crate":"munts_rp2040_firmware_embedded","version":"2.24840.1","id":"475a734ef5ac3f8c","name":"Ada.Synchronous_Task_Control","qualified_name":"Ada.Synchronous_Task_Control","kind":"ada_package","location":{"file":"../../../home/runner/.local/share/alire/builds/embedded_rp2040_15.3.0_860ea34a/0b5b32120df8a3ef486d57e8668a7b1b8eaeb4016de40c4c2ac49d41bc4ad171/gnarl/a-sytaco.ads","line":50,"column":9},"code":"package Ada.Synchronous_Task_Control","documentation":{"description":"This package provides the functionality defined in ARM D.10 for suspending\nand resuming tasks. Tasks can just suspend themselves (not allowed to\nsuspend another task), and any task can resume a suspended task. This\npackage has been specifically tailored to meet the Ravenscar Profile\nrestrictions on all bare board Ravenscar targets.\n\nThis package provides the functionality to change and query the status\nof a suspension object, and to block the calling task until the state of\nthe suspension object is set to ``True``."},"simple_types":[{"id":"004b8fb1cfc7da33","name":"Suspension_Object","qualified_name":"Ada.Synchronous_Task_Control.Suspension_Object","kind":"ada_simple_type","location":{"file":"../../../home/runner/.local/share/alire/builds/embedded_rp2040_15.3.0_860ea34a/0b5b32120df8a3ef486d57e8668a7b1b8eaeb4016de40c4c2ac49d41bc4ad171/gnarl/a-sytaco.ads","line":56,"column":9},"code":"type Suspension_Object is limited private with\n  Default_Initial_Condition;"}],"subprograms":[{"id":"f768b0eb1977ae7b","name":"Current_State","qualified_name":"Ada.Synchronous_Task_Control.Current_State","kind":"ada_function","location":{"file":"../../../home/runner/.local/share/alire/builds/embedded_rp2040_15.3.0_860ea34a/0b5b32120df8a3ef486d57e8668a7b1b8eaeb4016de40c4c2ac49d41bc4ad171/gnarl/a-sytaco.ads","line":69,"column":13},"code":"function Current_State (S : Suspension_Object) return Boolean"},{"id":"a3d75ff4acc301a8","name":"Set_False","qualified_name":"Ada.Synchronous_Task_Control